Derick David

At Klarna, I want to use my creativity, enthusiasm,
and passion to make paying as simple, safe,
and above all, smooooth as possible.

Product Designer - I create human-centric experiences that tell stories, move people...and mountains.

My path.

My deep passion for design started at my tenure Apple's Developer Academy in Italy where I got a chance to work on multiple app projects collaborating with Apple mentors, multidisciplinary, and cross-functional teams coming from all over Europe. This is where I had hands-on experience UI design, UX research, and product development.

Recently, I’ve worked as a product and UI/UX designer at Stanford University where I collaborated with award-winning talent from Washington Post and Business Insider to build SaaS platforms that help rebuild trust in journalism in Silicon Valley. I also went to Iowa State University where I majored in Computer Science.

My design work including visual, brand identity, and graphic has reached more than 100,000 worldwide, including an astronaut in ISS!

Working at Klarna.

I love Klarna's way of working. It reminds me exactly of my way of working in my previous experiences. Starting from the iterate, refine, improve, and go live part up to treating failure as an invitation to do better next time. Also looking forward to working with a diverse group of people! Additionally, investing on the education of your people and on their mental health deserves big credit.

Something I’m unreasonably passionate about.

I have a passion for beautifully designed products that help humanity thrive and for coaching and leading people so that they become a better version of themselves. I love talking about entrepreneurship, mindfulness, and modern technology.

I like to shoot guns in my free time, I’ve been a told that I’m a naturally gifted shooter with crazy reflexes both in video games and real life.

A day in my life.

I read my favorite books and write about new ideas on my blog (I usually spend more time thinking clickbait-y titles) Engage on Twitter and Linkedin to grow my network and find memes that make me laugh 1 hour intense workout with two servings of protein shake

3 takes on Klarna.

My favorite Leadership Principle is...

Science can’t change the world on its own. The world needs to be willing to change. And it takes leaders. Leaders who are willing to chip away at the obstacles, cut through the noise and play the game. And win the game.

The best task of the day is ..

Connect to people, listen to their stories, and make them feel better about themselves. Also conducting some user interviews, usability tests, and field studies.

I’d describe my future team as...

Multidiscplinary, diverse, and high-energy, because I believe that's when magic happens.

My success story at Klarna starts here.

Your Privacy

When you visit any website, it may store or retrieve information on your browser, mostly in the form of cookies. This information might be about you, your preferences or your device, and is mostly used to make the site work as you expect it to. The information doesn't usually directly identify you, but it can give you a more personalized experience. Because we respect your right to privacy, you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. Click on the different category headings to find out more and change our default settings. However, blocking some types of cookies may impact your experience of the site and the services we're able to offer.

Necessary tracking technologies

Always Active

These tracking technologies are necessary for the website to function and can’t be switched off in our systems. You can set your browser to block or alert you about these tracking technologies, but it could result in parts of the site not working properly.

Performance tracking technologies

These tracking technologies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us know which pages are the most and least popular, and see how visitors move around the site. They also help us understand where our users are coming from. If these tracking technologies are declined, no user specific information related to our site performance will be stored.

Targeting tracking technologies

These tracking technologies may be set and used by our advertising partners to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites. They don’t store personal data, but are based on uniquely identifying your browser and internet device. If you don’t allow these tracking technologies, you will experience less targeted advertising.

Functional/Personalization tracking technologies

These tracking technologies enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalisation to make the content of the site more specific for you as a user. If you don’t allow these tracking technologies, all of the functions we use to personalise the site will not function properly.
